p.s:
(
petit déjeuner
) in France is n't the most important meal of the day , and is usually very light .

They often consist of an appetiser (
entrée
or
hors d'œuvre
) , a main dish (
plat
) , and a dessert (
dessert
) or cheese .

item.s:
(
pain
) is the classical side order in France .

(
fromage
) comes in hundreds of varieties , and can be included in most dishes .

(
Southwest France
) : beans , duck , pork & sausages

, or sauerkraut (
Alsace
) : stripped fermented cabbage + pork

(
Burgundy
) : pieces of beef ( in boiled oil ) , usually served with a selection of various sauces .

(
Rhône-Alpes
) : oven-roasted slices of potatoes with sour cream and cheese

(
Savoie
) : Melted Reblochon cheese , potatoes and pork or bacon .
